headline: SUI Slides as Token Unlock Concerns Trigger Breakdown to as Low as $2.27
summary: A 160% spike in trading volume and stop-loss cascades drove the plunge, with SUI stabilizing just above key support amid mounting November supply concerns.

headline: EA (EA) Margin Compression Challenges Bullish Narrative Despite Strong Earnings Outlook
summary: Electronic Arts (EA) posted annual earnings growth averaging 3.2% over the past five years, while recent net profit margins have narrowed to 12.1% from 14.1% a year ago. Looking forward, analysts forecast EA’s earnings to grow at 16.5% per year, outpacing the broader US market’s 15.6% rate. However, revenue growth of 5.2% still lags market expectations.
